/*
Bytecode in Java is a set of instructions 
for the Java Virtual Machine. 
Bytecode is a platform-independent code. 
Bytecode is a code that lies between low-level 
language and high-level language. 
After the Java code is compiled, 
the bytecode gets generated, 
which can be executed on any machine using JVM.*/